    <text id="A9818T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>William Martin arranges to meet with Alexander H. H. Stuart on a matter that
                    makes Martin "extremely anxious."</p>
            </div1>
        </front>

        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1867-01-16"><abbr expan="January">Jany </abbr>16<hi rend="super">th</hi> 1867</date>
                        <name type="place"><unclear>Henry </unclear>County</name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute>Dear Sir,</salute>
                </opener>

                <p>I wrote some days since suggesting that we would meet in Richmond on the 14<hi
                        rend="super">th</hi> of <abbr expan="February">Feby</abbr>, but <orig
                        reg="today">to day</orig> I received your letter proposing the 1<hi
                        rend="super">st</hi> of <unclear>Feby </unclear>. My engagements compel me
                    to be at Henry &amp; Franklin <abbr expan="February">Feby</abbr> courts on
                    the 1<hi rend="super">st</hi> &amp; 2<hi rend="super">nd</hi> Mondays. So I
                    hope it may suit the convienence of yourself &amp; Mr. <orig reg="Janney"
                        >Jany</orig> to meet me at the Balland House on the 14<hi rend="super"
                    >th</hi> as I am extremely anxious to see you.</p>

                <closer>
                    <salute>Yours Truly,</salute>
                    <signed><abbr expan="William">W<hi rend="super">m</hi></abbr> Martin</signed>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
